A '''denailer''' is a [[tool]] for removing [[Nail (fastener)|nails]] from [[lumber]] to facilitate its reuse. Two types of ''denailer'' are available:{{citation needed|date=October 2016}}

* A stationary ''denailer'' is a machine designed for single-purpose use, e.g. [[pallet]] refurbishing. 
* A ''portable denailer'' is a hand-held [[pneumatics|pneumatically-powered]] tool. It works by driving out the nail from the point end in pieces of nailed lumber which have been pried apart. The process of '''denailing''' (removing large numbers of nails from salvaged lumber) is greatly expedited by using this specialized tool.<ref name=GuyFalk>{{cite book|last=Falk|first=Bob & Guy, Brad|title=Unbuilding : salvaging the architectural treasures of unwanted houses|year=2007|publisher=Taunton|location=Newtown, CT|isbn=978-1-56158-825-1|pages=230–234}}</ref>

==See also==
* [[cat's paw (nail puller)]], an unpowered tool for removing nails

